  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Tests allow developers to prove that the code they write is working as expected.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If code isn’t working correctly, bug trackers are often used to track the work",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "necessary to fix the underlying problem. It’s often useful to associate",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "specific bugs with tests that reproduce them or verify they are fixed.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "“Bugs” as described in this document may also be referred to as",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "“issues.” To avoid confusion with the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://org.swift.testing/documentation/Testing/Issue",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " type in the testing library,",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "this document consistently refers to them as “bugs.”",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Associate-a-bug-with-a-test",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Associate a bug with a test",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To associate a bug with a test, use one of these functions:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "identifier": "doc://org.swift.testing/documentation/Testing/Trait/bug(_:_:)",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "type": "reference"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "identifier": "doc://org.swift.testing/documentation/Testing/Trait/bug(_:id:_:)-10yf5",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "type": "reference"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "identifier": "doc://org.swift.testing/documentation/Testing/Trait/bug(_:id:_:)-3vtpl",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "type": "reference"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The first argument to these functions is a URL representing the bug in its",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "bug-tracking system:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "@Test(\"Food truck engine works\", .bug(\"https://www.example.com/issues/12345\"))",
            "func engineWorks() async {",
            "  var foodTruck = FoodTruck()",
            "  await foodTruck.engine.start()",
            "  #expect(foodTruck.engine.isRunning)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can also specify the bug’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "unique identifier",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " in its bug-tracking system in",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "addition to, or instead of, its URL:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "@Test(",
            "  \"Food truck engine works\",",
            "  .bug(id: \"12345\"),",
            "  .bug(\"https://www.example.com/issues/67890\", id: 67890)",
            ")",
            "func engineWorks() async {",
            "  var foodTruck = FoodTruck()",
            "  await foodTruck.engine.start()",
            "  #expect(foodTruck.engine.isRunning)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A bug’s URL is passed as a string and must be parseable according to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3986.txt",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". A bug’s unique identifier",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "can be passed as an integer or as a string. For more information on the formats",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "recognized by the testing library, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://org.swift.testing/documentation/Testing/BugIdentifiers",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-titles-to-associated-bugs",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Add titles to associated bugs",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A bug’s unique identifier or URL may be insufficient to uniquely and clearly",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "identify a bug associated with a test. Bug trackers universally provide a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "“title” field for bugs that is not visible to the testing library. To add a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "bug’s title to a test, include it after the bug’s unique identifier or URL:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "@Test(",
            "  \"Food truck has napkins\",",
            "  .bug(id: \"12345\", \"Forgot to buy more napkins\")",
            ")",
            "func hasNapkins() async {",
            "  ...",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
